HEADWORD: off-the-rack
<hw>off-the-rack</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Intended to be worn without
alterations; ready-to-wear; -- of clothing. Contrasted with
<ant>made-to-order</ant>, <er>custom-made</er>.</def> <see>See
<er>pret-a-porter</er></see>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> off-the-shelf, ready-to-wear,
pret-a-porter.</syn>⟦br⟧
